Networking 6/7 troubleshooting 

? Why troubleshoot 
- Ensure smooth operation 
- Identify and fix network problems 
- Minimise downtime 
- Minimal distruption 

? Common Network Issues 
- Connectivity Loss - hardware , wifi etc 
- Slow network performance 
- IP Address conflicts - same device end up with the same IP address - confusion and connection issues 
- DNS resolution issues 

? identify symptoms 
- Observe the problem - slow , connectivity , files not appearing etc 
- Ex. Connectivity loss - symptoms = device can’t access network - diagnose by : check physical connection, verify network configuration ( routers / network settings etc , test with ping command [ ping google.com ]

? Network Tools - debugging 
1. Ping command - testing connectivity between 2 devices 
 - ping [ IP address or domain ] / ping google.com        = response from domain if working 


2. Traceroute - tracks the distance/ route your data/traffic  takes to reach a specific destination
- traceroute [domain] / traceroute google.com        = response from domain if working 


3. NsLookup - DNS - to find an ip address associated with a domain name  
- nslookup domain / nslookup google.com              = response from domain if working 


Example = i can’t reach a website , how can I troubleshoot ?  ( double check )
- Check network connectivity - working wifi connection 
- ping command 
- Nslookup 
- Check host file - no overriding entries 
- Firewall not blocking incoming/outgoing traffic
- Close browser 
- Check DNS cache - clear if needed 
- Check traceroute 
